title.narrative: USAID/WA Trade Hub and African Partners Network Project II

description.narrative: With funding from USAID, we work with West African businesses to boost regional and global trade by improving the capacity of West Africas private sector and business enabling environment. The Trade Hub promotes more regional trade in key commodities like maize, livestock and rice to address food security, and reduces poverty by boosting globally traded value-added exports like cashews, mango, shea, and apparel. The Trade Hub works through and in collaboration with a network of regional African partners.
